Description

FK SJM-T/SJF-T/SRSM-T Series rod ends feature 3-piece precision stainless steel construction. These self-lubricating, high-strength rod ends feature bodies and races composed of 17-4PH CRES heat-treated stainless steel and a 440C CRES heat-treated stainless steel ball. FK SJM-T/SJF-T/SRSM-T Series rod ends come standard with a PTFE fabric liner bonded to the race i. d.

FK weldable tube ends are very useful for the fabrication of suspension links, wishbones, and linkages. They're available in a variety of sizes in either right or left hand thread applications to best suit your vehicle needs. These tube ends are made from chromoly steel for easy weldability to common DOM material and, as with any fabrication part, proper welding technique is a must!

FK CM/CF Series rod ends are economy rod ends featuring 2-piece, metal-to-metal construction. Their bodies are made using low carbon steel that's zinc plated and chromate-treated, and their balls are made of 52100 hard chrome plated steel. These high-quality rod ends are often used in street rod applications without high-impact or load requirements. Optional PTFE liners are available.

ULT. Static Radial Load (lbs. ): 20, 250 lbs.
Rod End Bearing Material: Stainless steel
Notes: Grooved bearing.
Description

FK precision wide series spherical bearings are a great choice for fabricating long travel suspension arms and links. These strong, dependable spherical bearings are heat-treated stainless steel with a bonded PTFE liner to handle abuse. FK's self-lubricating PTFE liners are chemically bonded to the inner diameter of the race to offer a very high load-carrying capacity with greatly increased dynamic wear characteristics. They are available in plain or grooved styles. Wide series spherical bearings offer the best American-made quality because FK knows that in order to finish first, you must first finish.

You won't think about that bargain rod end--until it breaks. Can you afford that? Choose FK HRSMX-T/HIN-T Series rod ends.

Their durable 52100 steel balls are heat-treated and hard chrome plated. RSMX Series rod ends' steel alloy races are heat-treated, zinc plated, and chromate treated for additional strength. Self-lubricating PTFE liners are available with these rod ends.

Description

FK weldable tube ends are very useful for the fabrication of suspension links, wishbones, and linkages. They're available in a variety of sizes in either right or left hand thread applications to best suit your vehicle needs. These tube ends are made from chromoly steel for easy weldability to common DOM material and, as with any fabrication part, proper welding technique is a must!

Description
